I LOVE this diner. Firstly, they have tried and true, REAL homemade corned beef hash, not canned, not frozen. That alone puts them way above ANY other diner in the area. The food is cheap, deliscious, and consistent quality. Absolutely lovely waitstaff, many of which I’ve seen there for years. The menu still makes me laugh, even after 10 years of going there. We haven’t dined in since COVID started, but because we missed the food, we’ve started getting brunch take out and it was the best decision ever. They could definitely use a tech upgrade for check out/ take out, but a little extra time to process your card is a small price to pay for this charming, classic diner experience. I urge anyone who loves diner food to show them some love and at least order out. Tip generously! They work hard and deserve it
